<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1387,1629]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1387,1412]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is close to 
<taxonomicName box="[559,703,1388,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Sigmuncus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albigrisea">
<emphasis box="[559,703,1388,1412]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. albigrisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Besides the differences mentioned above, there is also a black patch at the tornus of the forewing in 
<taxonomicName box="[572,686,1424,1448]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Sigmuncus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arcuata">
<emphasis box="[572,686,1424,1448]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. arcuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but no black patch in 
<taxonomicName box="[942,1083,1424,1448]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Sigmuncus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albigrisea">
<emphasis box="[942,1083,1424,1448]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. albigrisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
