<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1387,1629]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,350,1495,1520]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[357,424,1495,1519]" name="China" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">China</collectingCountry>
(Hainan, 
<collectingCountry box="[535,670,1495,1520]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[689,749,1495,1519]" name="India" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">India</collectingCountry>
, Southeast Asia. The species was reported for 
<collectingCountry box="[1270,1337,1495,1519]" name="China" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">China</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ades" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refString="Ades, G. W. J. &amp; Kendrick, R. C. (2004) Hong Kong Fauna: A Checklist of Selected Taxa. Second Edition. Fauna Conservation Department, Kadoorie Farm &amp; Botanic Garden Corporation, Hong Kong. 84 pp." type="book" year="2004">
Ades &amp; Kendrick (
<number box="[299,361,1532,1556]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1387,1629]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,1568,1592]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Poole" box="[322,469,1567,1591]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refString="Poole, R. W. (1989) Noctuidae. In: Heppner, J. B. (Ed.). J. B. Lepidopterum Catalogus. New Series, Fascicle 118. E. J. Brill / Flora &amp; Fauna Publications, Leiden-New York-Copenhagen-Koln, 1314 pp." type="book" year="1989">
Poole (
<number box="[403,461,1567,1591]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1989.0">1989</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reffered this species as a 
<taxonomicName box="[768,861,1568,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Gyrtona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[768,861,1568,1591]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Gyrtona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on the wing patterns and the genitalia, we follow the treatment of 
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway" box="[415,609,1604,1628]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refString="Holloway, J. D. (1985) Moths of Borneo, part 14: Family Noctuidae: Subfamilies Euteliinae, Stictopterinae, Plusiinae, Pantheinae. Malayan Nature Journal, 38, 157 - 317." type="journal article" year="1985">
Holloway (
<number box="[541,601,1604,1628]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1985.0">1985</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, placed it to the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[866,987,1605,1628]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Sigmuncus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[866,987,1605,1628]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Sigmuncus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
